All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AESUtils
The AESUtils class provides utility methods for encrypting and decrypting strings using the AES (Advanced Encryption Standard) symmetric encryption algorithm.
Applicant
The Applicant class represents an applicant in the system.
ApplicantBehavior
Defines the behavior specific to users with the applicant role.
ApplicantMenu
Interface representing the menu options available to applicant.
ApplicantProjectHandler
The ApplicantProjectHandler class extends the ProjectHandler class and handles operations related to applicants and their interaction with projects.
ApplicantUI
The ApplicantUI class implements the ApplicantMenu interface and handles the user interface for an applicant.
ApplicationForm
The ApplicationForm class represents an application made by an Applicant for a specific project.
BTO_app
The BTO_app class serves as the entry point for the Build-To-Order (BTO) application system.
CommonMenu
Common menu interface that defines basic operations for all user roles in the system, such as displaying the main menu and logging out.
CSVImporter
The CSVImporter class is responsible for importing various entities from CSV files into the system.
CSVWriter
The CSVWriter class provides methods for writing different entities to CSV files.
Database
The Database class holds static lists that store instances of various entities in the application, including applicants, managers, officers, projects, enquiries, flat bookings, and application history.
Enquiry
The Enquiry class represents a question or message submitted by an applicant regarding a specific project or general enquiry.
EnquiryHandler
The EnquiryHandler class is responsible for managing enquiries related to projects or general queries.
FlatBooking
The FlatBooking class represents a booking made by an applicant for a housing flat.
InputValidation
The InputValidation class provides generic and specialized methods for validating and parsing user input from the console.
InputValidation.InputParser<T>
A functional interface for parsing strings into type T.
Login
Handles the login functionality for different types of users including applicants, officers, and managers.
Manager
The Manager class extends the UserAccount class and represents a manager responsible for overseeing a housing project.
ManagerMenu
Interface for manager menu options in the BTO system.
ManagerUI
The ManagerUI class implements the ManagerMenu interface and handles the user interface for a manager.
Officer
The Officer class extends the Applicant class and represents an officer who manages projects.
OfficerBehavior
Defines the behavior specific to users with the officer role.
OfficerMenu
Interface for officer menu actions in the BTO system.
OfficerUI
The OfficerUI class implements the OfficerMenu interface and handles the user interface for an officer.
Project
The Project class represents a project with various attributes such as project name,neighborhood, unit types, sell prices and many more.
ProjectHandler
The ProjectHandler class is responsible for managing a list of projects.
RegistrationForm
The RegistrationForm class represents a registration form submitted by an officer to register for a housing project.
RoleBehavior
Defines the behavior for different user roles in the system.
UserAccount
The UserAccount class is an abstract representation of a user in the system.
UserMenuHandler
The UserMenuHandler class is responsible for handling the user interface related to the menu display.
WithdrawalRequest
The WithdrawalRequest class represents a request made by an applicant to withdraw from a previously submitted application.
